<subSubSection id="43946579FFD68512FF191A07FD88E15D" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0B3136F2FFD68512FF191A07FD88E15D" blockId="4.[151,1437,266,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="39FAEAE0FFD68512FF191A07FE92E245" bold="true" box="[151,279,266,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="CC8E4D71FFD68512FEAE1A07FDBBE242" box="[288,574,266,291]" class="Insecta" family="Athericidae" genus="Dasyomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysopilum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="39FAEAE0FFD68512FEAE1A07FDBBE242" box="[288,574,266,291]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Dasyomma chrysopilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="39FAEAE0FFD68512FDC61A07FD22E245" bold="true" box="[584,679,266,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="22C9579BFFD68512FDC61A07FD22E245" box="[584,679,266,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be immediately separated from all other known species of the genus by having dense, semi-appressed golden pilosity on the abdominal tergites (
<figureCitation id="93B52A77FFD68512FB131A3FFA95E22D" box="[1181,1296,306,332]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1968,1992]" captionTargetBox="[186,1366,629,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[181,1406,629,1961]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Dasyomma chrysopilum, sp. nov. 5, male holotype, dorsal view. 6, male holotype, lateral view. 7, female paratype, dorsal view. 8, female paratype, semilateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/176053/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">
Figs. 
<number id="BD4624D5FFD68512FB6F1A3FFA95E22D" box="[1249,1296,306,332]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" value="6.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="5.0">5–8</number>
</figureCitation>
), clearly an autapomorphic character state. It fits in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="CC8E4D71FFD68512FCAB1A57FC2CE212" box="[805,937,346,371]" class="Insecta" family="Athericidae" genus="Dasyomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="39FAEAE0FFD68512FCAB1A57FC2CE212" box="[805,937,346,371]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Dasyomma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as recognized by Malloch, as it has fine black setae along vein CuA where it forms the posterior border of cell 
<emphasis id="39FAEAE0FFD68512FC471A8FFC68E2FA" box="[969,1005,386,411]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">bm</emphasis>
. In Malloch’s (
<number id="BD4624D5FFD68512FB101A8FFB5EE2FD" box="[1182,1243,386,412]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" value="1932.0">1932</number>
) key, 
<taxonomicName id="CC8E4D71FFD68512FAAF1A8FFF5FE2A2" class="Insecta" family="Athericidae" genus="Dasyomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysopilum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="39FAEAE0FFD68512FAAF1A8FFF5FE2A2" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">D. chrysopilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="39FAEAE0FFD68512FF6F1AA7FEBAE2A5" bold="true" box="[225,319,426,452]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="22C9579BFFD68512FF6F1AA7FEBAE2A5" box="[225,319,426,452]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
keys to couplet 
<number id="BD4624D5FFD68512FD8E1AA7FD8AE2A5" box="[512,527,426,452]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" value="2.0">2</number>
but then does not fit either half of that couplet because of the abdominal coloration that is black but not at all glossy. In Coscarón &amp; Coscarón’s (
<number id="BD4624D5FFD68512FC4E1ADFFC78E28D" box="[960,1021,466,492]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" value="1995.0">1995</number>
) key, the female of 
<taxonomicName id="CC8E4D71FFD68512FB691ADFFA19E28A" box="[1255,1436,466,491]" class="Insecta" family="Athericidae" genus="Dasyomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysopilum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="39FAEAE0FFD68512FB691ADFFA19E28A" box="[1255,1436,466,491]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">D. chrysopilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="39FAEAE0FFD68512FF191AF7FF71E175" bold="true" box="[151,244,506,532]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="22C9579BFFD68512FF191AF7FF71E175" box="[151,244,506,532]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
keys to 
<taxonomicName id="CC8E4D71FFD68512FED81AF7FDC1E175" authority="Philippi" authorityName="Philippi" box="[342,580,506,532]" class="Insecta" family="Athericidae" genus="Dasyomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvum">
<emphasis id="39FAEAE0FFD68512FED81AF7FE4FE172" box="[342,458,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">D. fulvum</emphasis>
(Philippi)
</taxonomicName>
, but the male does not key beyond couplet 
<number id="BD4624D5FFD68512FBB21AF7FBCEE175" box="[1084,1099,506,532]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" value="6.0">6</number>
because the body color does not fit either part of the couplet.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="5FF1667AFFD68512FF191CBDFCDAE48B" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/176053/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" targetBox="[186,1366,629,1934]" targetPageId="4">
